  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6813.66 sitting above the GEX flip at 6801 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and will sell any rallies while buying dips, creating strong mean-reversion forces. The massive positive gamma wall at 6830 (+75.6B) represents a key resistance level where dealer selling pressure will intensify significantly, while the thick stack of positive gamma between 6810-6830 should act as magnetic price support. Given spot is trading in the heart of this positive gamma zone with over 315B total GEX, expect muted volatility and range-bound action between 6801 flip level and the 6830 resistance wall.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect choppy sideways trading between 6800-6830 with dealers capping big moves.",
